Direct Known Subclasses:
HeavyWeightPlace
public class Place extends GraphElement implements com.telenav.mesakit.map.geography.Located, com.telenav.mesakit.map.geography.shape.rectangle.Bounded, com.telenav.mesakit.map.geography.shape.rectangle.Intersectable, Comparable<Place>, Serializable
A place marks geographical areas such as towns, cities and neighborhoods with a point location, usually in the center of the area. Places can be retrieved with:

Graph Query

  • Graph.places()
  • Graph.placesWithNonZeroPopulation()
  • Graph.placesWithPopulationOfAtLeast(Count)
  • Graph.placeForIdentifier(PlaceIdentifier)
Spatial Search
  • Graph.placeNear(Location)
  • Graph.placesNear(Location, Count, Distance, Count)
  • Graph.placesInside(Rectangle)
  • Graph.placesInside(Region)

Places have a name(), a type() and a location that can be retrieved through Located.location(). They are also Intersectable and Bounded with a zero-sized rectangle that can be expanded, and they are Validatable.

Author:
jonathanl (shibo)
